Diagnosis.
Body black (
Fig. 25
); eye in dorsal view 1.3 × as long as temple (
Fig. 26I
); eye in lateral view 1.3 × higher than wide (
Fig. 26K
); frons with some rugae around antennal sockets and setae near antennal sockets (
Fig. 26I
); vertex and temple smooth; face rugose and with some punctures, 1.5 × wider than high, rather convex medially and with a longitudinal ridge (
Fig. 26J
); clypeus small, semi-elliptical and some punctures (
Fig. 26J
); precoxal sulcus widely crenulate, reaching middle coxa and anterior edge of epicnemial area (
Fig. 26C
); notauli incomplete and short, only present anteriorly; medio-posterior depression deep and droplet-shaped, not extending to middle of mesoscutum (
Fig. 26D
); surface of propodeum densely reticulate-rugose, areola absent posteriorly; pterostigma wide, 4.2 × longer than its maximum width (
Fig. 26A
); hind coxa smooth (
Fig. 25
); length of first tergite 1.4 × its apical width, its surface longitudinally striate, its dorsal carinae separated posteriorly (
Fig. 26E
); setose part of ovipositor sheath 0.2 × as long as fore wing (total visible sheath 0.3 times), and 0.7 × as long as hind tibia (
Fig. 26H
); antenna and metasoma except first tergite dark brown; palpi yellow; mandible, ventral side of coxa and femur yellowish brown; dorsal side of coxa, femur, apex of hind tibia and whole tarsus reddish brown (
Fig. 25
).

Head. Transverse, width of head 1.9 × its lateral length, and 1.3 × wider than mesoscutum (
Fig. 26I
); antenna with 38 antennomere, third antennomere (including annellus) 1.4 × longer than fourth antennomere, length of third, fourth and penultimate antennomere4.0, 2.2 and 2.5 × their width, respectively (
Fig. 26G
); length of maxillary palp 1.6 × height of head (
Fig. 25
); eye in dorsal view 1.3 × as long as temple; eye in lateral view 1.3 × higher than wide (
Fig. 26I
); frons with some rugae around antennal sockets and setae near antennal sockets (
Fig. 26I
); vertex and temple smooth; OOL:diameter of ocellus:POL= 10:3:4; face rugose and with some punctures, 1.5 × wider than high, rather convex medially and with a longitudinal ridge (
Fig. 26J
); clypeus small, semi-elliptical and with some punctures (
Fig. 26J
); mandible enlarged apically, dorsal tooth enlarged, lobe-shaped (
Fig. 26L
), ventral tooth medium-sized and lobe-shaped (
Fig. 26M
), middle tooth curved and acute, with incision between first and second tooth (
Fig. 26L
), medial length of mandible 1.6 × its maximum width.

Mesosoma. Length of mesosoma 1.4 × its height (
Fig. 26C
); pronope absent; medio-anteriorly pronotum widely crenulate, remainder of pronotum weakly rugose; epicnemial area crenulated; precoxal sulcus widely crenulate, reaching middle coxa and anterior edge of epicnemial area (
Fig. 26C
); pleural sulcus narrowly crenulated; episternal scrobe linear and deep; metapleuron largely smooth, but reticulate-rugose ventrally (
Fig. 26C
); middle lobe of mesoscutum densely setose (
Fig. 26D
); notauli incomplete and short, only present anteriorly (
Fig. 26D
); medio-posterior depression deep and droplet-shaped, not extending to middle of mesoscutum, scutellar sulcus deep and rugose, with three short carinae, sulcus 3.0 × wider than its maximum length (
Fig. 26D
); scutellum smooth; surface of propodeum densely reticulate-rugose, areola absent posteriorly (
Fig. 26E
).

Wings (
Figs 26A–B
). Pterostigma wide, 4.2 × longer than its maximum width. r:3-SR:SR1 = 1:4:14; 1-SR+M slightly sinuate; SR1 straight; r 0.5 × as long as width of pterostigma; cu-a postfurcal; 1-CU1:2-CU1 = 3: 20; 3- CU1 as long as CU1b; 2-SR:3-SR:r-m = 21:19:11; m-cu postfurcal, converging to 1-M posteriorly; first subdiscal cell 3.3 × as long as wide; M+CU1 largely unsclerotized. Hind wing: M+CU: 1-M: 1r-m = 4:3:2; m-cu weakly postfurcal.

Legs. Hind coxa smooth (
Fig. 26E
), without ventro-basal tubercle, densely setose; tarsal claws moderately slender, as long as arolium (
Fig. 26N
); length of femur, tibia and basitarsus of hind leg 3.8, 7.8 and 3.3 × their width, respectively; apical appendages of hind tarsal segments absent, but segments ventrally with dense bristles (
Fig. 26N
).

