subSubSection.paragraph:
Metasoma. Length of first tergite 1.4 × its apical width, its surface longitudinally striate, its dorsal carinae separated posteriorly (
Fig. 26E
); dorsope distinct; setose part of ovipositor sheath 0.2 × as long as fore wing (total visible sheath 0.3 times), and 0.7 × as long as hind tibia (
Fig. 26H
).

Colour. Black (
Fig. 25
); antenna and metasoma except first tergite dark brown; palpi yellow; mandible, ventral side of coxa and femur yellowish brown; dorsal side of coxa, femur and apical hind tibia and whole tarsus reddish brown; pterostigma and veins brown; wing membrane hyaline.
